Narrative:
On February [XXX], 2025 at 6:22 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a bus in a traffic circle on [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was traveling northbound around a traffic circle on [XXX] in the left lane with a bus traveling next to the Waymo AV in the right lane. As the Waymo AV began to turn left around the traffic circle, the bus also began to turn and crossed into the left lane and the driver side of the bus made contact with the front passenger side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On January [XXX], 2025 at 2:21 AM MT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Scottsdale, Arizona was in a collision involving an SUV at a passenger drop-off lane near [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was traveling northwest in the right side passenger drop-off lane at [XXX] when it approached an SUV stopped in the left side drop-off lane.  As the Waymo AV was passing the SUV, the back passenger side door of the SUV opened and made contact with the rear driver side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On August [XXX], 2023 at 4:39 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Santa Monica, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on [XXX] at [XXX].
The Waymo AV was traversing a roundabout at the intersection of [XXX] at [XXX] when it slowed to a stop for other vehicles approaching and in the roundabout. The front of the passenger car that was in the roundabout behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

A Zoox vehicle was traveling through a hotel loading zone, when the driver's side door of a stopped passenger vehicle in the right adjacent lane opened, and made contact with the front right sensor of the Zoox vehicle. There were no injuries and the police were not called. Autonomy was engaged in the 30 second period prior to the collision.
